## Canary Metrics — pass/fail pre-conditions

These are **gates, not deductions.** Every metric must pass before QR scoring runs. A
chapter that fails any metric is returned for rework. They are **measured, not estimated** —
the QR workflow runs `scripts/canary.py` against the chapter file, which computes each value
deterministically and compares it to the thresholds below (with any genre/custom overrides
from project.json). The same chapter always yields the same numbers. The Writing and Polish
prompts target these same thresholds from the first draft.

| Metric | Threshold | Pass when |
|---|---|---|
| Passive voice | < {{PASSIVE_VOICE}}% | below |
| Emotion tells | < {{EMOTION_TELLS}}% | below |
| Weak adverbs | < {{WEAK_ADVERBS}}/1k words | below |
| Sentence variety (std dev) | >= {{SENTENCE_VARIETY}} | at or above |
| Complex paragraphs | < {{COMPLEX_PARAGRAPHS}}% | below |
| Readability (FK grade) | <= {{FK_GRADE}} | at or below |
| Glue index | < {{GLUE_INDEX}}% | below |

*Author override: a specific Canary failure may be overridden with a documented reason
(e.g. deliberately fragmented prose failing sentence variety). The override is noted in the
QR report and scoring proceeds as if the metric passed. See QR.md.*
